<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KENNEDY-HOSTAGES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GUNMAN HOLDS PILOTS HOSTAGE AT KENNEDY; PASSENGERS FREED
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Nev.)  By ANDY NEWMAN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A man armed with a handgun rushed onto a National
Airlines jet at Kennedy International Airport Thursday night and
took the pilot and co-pilot hostage, a spokesman for the Port
Authority of New York and New Jersey said.
</P>
<P>
   All the passengers on the plane were released unharmed, said
Greg Trevor, the Port Authority spokesman. One passenger described
a scene of pandemonium.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly before 11 p.m., the gunman rushed the cockpit of the
National Airlines Flight 19, a Boeing 757 that was scheduled to
take off at 9:30 p.m., bound for Las Vegas, Trevor said.
</P>
<P>
   It was not clear how the man got the gun through airport
security, Trevor said. ``That's a very good question,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The plane was at the airport's Terminal 4, at Gate 33, the Port
Authority said. No injuries were immediately reported.
</P>
<P>
   A man who answered the phone at National Airlines' toll-free
reservation number said, ``We have no comment and no numbers for
you to call,'' then hung up.
</P>
<P>
   Misty Nichols, a passenger on the flight, said that the plane
was supposed to leave at 9:30 p.m., but that she boarded after 10.
</P>
<P>
   ``I sat down, got buckled up and the next thing I know everybody
was screaming,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Then, people started rushing to get off the plane, she said, and
that a little girl got trampled in the rush.
</P>
<P>
   She later tried to retrieve some of her belongings, but someone
yelled, ``Get off the plane _ your life is more important than your
stuff.''
</P>
<P>
   National, formed a year ago and based in Las Vegas, is a small
airline, with a fleet of 11 Boeing 757-200s providing nonstop
service from Las Vegas to eight other cities. But it is growing
fast. It began turning a profit in March, after only 10 months in
the air, becoming one of the fastest new airlines in history to
make money, according to Aviation Daily.
</P>
<P>
   National runs four flights a day from Kennedy Airport to Las
Vegas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
