<SLUG> BC-ZCOM-EXCITE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WEB STUDIO MAKES JUMP TO HIGH SPEED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JESSE HIESTAND 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; BURBANK, Calif. _ Z.com, a Burbank Web studio backed by key
Hollywood investors, announced Thursday it will team with leading
broadband provider ExciteHome to showcase its online entertainment
over high-speed cable and DSL lines.
</P>
<P>
   The site's original online comedy, film, animation, game and
live events will also give ExciteHome subscribers a taste of
real-time Web video and other new media fare geared to broadband,
company officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ``This gives us an opportunity to experiment with someone who is
leading the charge in bringing broadband to the home,'' said Z.com
Chief Executive Officer Joe DiNunzio. ``The exposure is incredibly
important to help a small start-up like us break through the
clutter.''
</P>
<P>
   Founding investors in Z.com, which grew out of Pasadena business
incubator idealab!, include film producer Jerry Bruckheimer,
Maverick Records partner and co-CEO Guy Oseary, talent management
firm 3 Arts Entertainment, and Basic Entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   The site launched in early June and will continue to roll out
new ``channels'' _ Web pages dedicated to particular Web shows,
specials or media _ throughout the summer, DiNunzio said.
</P>
<P>
   ExciteHome, based in Redwood City, Calif., has the nation's
largest customer base for high-speed Internet service, serving
about 1.5 million homes nationwide, including Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Content from companies like Z.com is intended to make the
service more appealing, said Jonathan Rosenberg, a senior vice
president with the service provider.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our leadership in broadband depends on our ability to provide
high-quality and compelling content to our subscribers,'' Rosenberg
said in a statement. ``Z.com greatly enhances the ExciteHome
service by delivering fresh and original content.''
</P>
<P>
   The Z.com content will be available to customers through the
Excite ClickVideo, a broadband video application accessed through
the Home connection.
</P>
<P>
   Other Internet users have access to the same content by going to
Z.com's regular Web page.
</P>
<P>
   The programming will include a video scrapbook of Ellen
DeGeneres' cross-country comedy tour; Z.com's popular reality game
show ``Dare for Dollars''; and ``Alanis Morissette _ The One
Tour,'' an 11-country musical and cultural journey.
</P>
<P>
   In return, ExciteHome will run Z.com advertising and promotion
across its network.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-28-00 0022EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
