   &QL; 
 &UR; ELECTION _  &LR; The Internet is offering you a chance to set the agenda
for the coming presidential debates.
</P>
<P>
   Through a Web site set up by the Commission on Presidential
Debates, you'll be able to suggest topics you would like to hear
discussed in the televised debates.  &UR; BY CARRIE KIRBY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; SYMANTEC _  &LR; Symantec, the maker of security software for personal
computers, said Thursday that it will acquire corporate security
software company Axent Technologies for $975 million in stock.
</P>
<P>
   If the deal is approved by shareholders, it will create a giant
in the computer security software industry serving both consumer
and corporate markets.  &UR; BY VERNE KOPYTOFF &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; CONSOLIDATED _  &LR; Taking advantage of the Bay Area real estate
run-up, Consolidated Freightways has sold its 2.3-acre Menlo Park,
Calif., headquarters for tens of millions of dollars and will move
to Washington state next month, the company announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Transferring its headquarters to a less-expensive area has a
secondary advantage of helping the trucking company recruit
employees who can't afford to live in the Bay Area, Consolidated
said.  &UR; BY CAROL EMERT &LR;
