<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards By Jimmy Chuang States News Service
Washington, July 28 -- Stein Seal Co. of Kulpsville won a $57,930
contract from the Defense Industrial Supply Center in Philadelphia
for hardware and abrasives.
</P>
<P>
   Litton Systems Inc. of Springfield won a $94,500 contract from
the U.S. Air Force in Tinker Air Force Base, Okla., for instruments
and laboratory equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $55,623 contract from
the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for pipe, tubing, hose
and fittings.
</P>
<P>
   Kampi Components Co. Inc. of Fairless Hilss won a $57,880
contract from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for
valves.
</P>
<P>
   Amp Inc. of Harrisburg won a $87,781 contract from the Defense
General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for electric wire and power
and distribution equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Ametek Inc. of Sellersville won a $97,845 contract from the
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for instruments and
laboratory equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Kampi Components Co. Inc. of Fairless Hills won a $64,398
contract from the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va.,
for instruments and laboratory equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Raytheon Co. of State College won a $516,767 contract from the
U.S. Air Force in Rome, N.Y., for research and development.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $81,054 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engines,
turbines and components.
</P>
<P>
   Derbyshire Machine and Tool Co. of Philadelphia won a $255,216
contract from the U.S. Navy in Mechanicsburg for valves.
</P>
<P>
   Haverford Systems of Dowington won a $65,021 contract from the
U.S. Naval Surface Warfare Center in Philadelphia for automatic
data processing and telecommunication services.
</P>
