<P>
   THE MAKING OF REAGAN'S VICE PRESIDENT
</P>
<P>
   HOW-REAGAN-PICKED-BUSH-CENTERPIECE _ At 5:30 p.m. on the third
evening of the 1980 Republican convention in Detroit, Texas Gov.
George W. Bush's father was barely on Ronald Reagan's radar screen.
Six hours later, he was Reagan's vice-presidential nominee _ and
the Bush dynasty was launched. From the front lines of the Reagan
Revolution, one man's account. By Richard V. Allen. (3,000 words.)
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of Ronald Reagan and George Bush are available
on Newscom or by calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.)
</P>
