<P>
   FUZZY LITTLE TEST TUBES
</P>
<P>
   GENETICS-MICE-CENTERPIECE _ Each year, ``mouse ranchers'' breed
millions of rodents genetically engineered to develop maladies
ranging from obesity to Down syndrome. Doomed to perish in
experiments, they may help scientists uncover the foundations of
human disease. By Lawrence Osborne. (2,400 words. A full-length
4,500-word version is available on request.)
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of genetically altered mice are available on
Newscom or by calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.)
</P>
<P>
   (Lawrence Osborne is a frequent contributor to The New York
Times Magazine.)
</P>
<P>
   THE INGRATIATOR: RICK LAZIO'S WINNING WAYS
</P>
<P>
   RICK-LAZIO-CENTERPIECE _ Rick Lazio is a politician who aims to
please _ whether courting moderate voters or the conservative House
leadership. He is not a man of ideas, but that may be just right
for a nonideological time. By James Traub. (3,20 words. A
full-length 7,200-word version is available on request.)
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos Rick Lazio are available on Newscom or by
calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.)
