<P>
   ANTIQUERS SEEKING AMERICANA FLOCK TO NEW HAMPSHIRE
</P>
<P>
   NH-ANTIQUES-LIFEBEAT _ A week-long show in Manchester, N.H.,
sponsored by the New Hampshire Antiques Dealers Associaton, has
become ``the antiquing highlight of the summer,'' according to one
collector. ``People plan vacations around this show and travel long
distances to get here,'' says another. This year's show will take
place from August 5 to 12, but even if you miss it, there are
interesting things to see in and around Manchester.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of antiques from last year's New Hampshire
shows available in JPEG format by calling William Gonzalez at
212-499-3355.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NOW YOU CAN TAKE YOUR OFFICE TO THE GYM
</P>
<P>
   WORKING-WORKOUT-LIFEBEAT_ Work is the latest thing in working
out. Pressed for time, more and more people are bringing their
briefcases to the gym and ``multitasking'' while on the treadmill
or exercise bike. Doctors think this detracts from the exercise
experience, one benefit of which is to reduce stress. However, gyms
are cooperating with their clients. Some have even attached
Netpulse stations (computers providing Internet access) to their
Lifecycles and Stairmasters. By Daphne Palmer Geanacopoulos.
</P>
<P>
   ONE HAND, ONE HEART
</P>
<P>
   JUST-ONE-HAND-LIFEBEAT _ In one second on a hot summer day in
1947, Mary Taylor Previte, now a New Jersey assemblywoman, lost her
left hand to a buzz saw. However, her parents wouldn't let her feel
sorry for herself. They encouraged her to do everything that she
would have done had the accident not occurred. Since then, she
recounts, whenever she does something that someone thought she
couldn't, ``something cheers inside.'' By Mary Taylor Previte.
</P>
<P>
   PETS THINK AND FEEL MORE THAN WE KNOW
</P>
<P>
   PETS-PSYCHOLOGY-LIFEBEAT _ Pets have both consciousness and
emotions. And one of the joys of living with them is catching a
glimpse of what makes them tick. Pets behave as they do for many
reasons. Why is your dog howling? Why isn't your cat eating? What's
the best way to housebreak your dog? The answers to these and other
questions are rooted in animal psychology. By Toni Gardner.
</P>
