<P>
   CONCORDE-CRASH _ GONESSE, France _ French investigators
discovered the body of a fifth victim under the rubble of a hotel
destroyed when an Air France Concorde crashed earlier this week,
raising the death toll to 114. The victim was not immediately
identified and the sex was not known. Four other people died on the
ground, all of them employees of the hotel. All 109 people on board
the supersonic jet died. The French Transport Ministry also said
that both tires on
</P>
<P>
   the aircraft exploded during takeoff apparently sending
fragments into the engines and possibly piercing the fuel tanks.
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location, Atlanta; Category, International; Subcategory,
Other.
