   ISRAEL-CLINTON _ JERUSALEM _ In an apparent attempt to shore up
the weak government of Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak, President
Bill Clinton gives an
</P>
<P>
   interview on Israeli TV Friday night. He's expected to put his
spin on the failed Camp David summit and express the U.S.'
continuing support for Israel.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier in the day, one Palestinian official said Clinton's
support for Barak is more aimed at the elections in the U.S. than
in Israel. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
