   PHILA-MAYOR-PROFILE (Philadelphia) _ A look at Mayor John Street
of Philadelphia. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file)
</P>
<P>
   ECON-REPORT (Undated) _ Economic growth surged 5.2 percent in
the second quarter because of increased investment by businesses
and robust, though slowing, spending by consumers, defying
expectations of a slowdown. By Louis Uchitelle.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-COSMETICS (Moscow) _ When Russia began picking apart its
economy in 1992, Oleg Nasobin spotted an opportunity. After 70
years of Soviet deficits, his country was brimming with pent-up
demand for lipstick, face creams and body lotion. It was a business
opportunity he could take up only by leaving. Now his company,
Green Mama, is one of Russia's top five cosmetics producers. By
Sabrina Tavernise.
</P>
<P>
   VIETNAM-STOCKS (Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam) _ Trading on
Vietnam's first stock market began Friday, but authorities limited
the prices of two companies, and just $5,000 of shares were traded.
By Wayne Arnold.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-U.S.-WTO (Dateline to come) _ The United States said it
would file a complaint against Mexico with the World Trade
Organization, accusing Mexico of failing to open its $12 billion
telecommunications market. (Staff byline to come)
</P>
<P>
   IVILLAGE-RESIGN (Undated) _ IVillage, the online women's
network, says Candice Carpenter, the company's co-founder, is
stepping down as chief executive. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
