<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``e'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LYRICS-EDIT (Undated) _ There has been a remarkable change in
the way record companies and radio stations now handle explicit
lyrics in pop songs. In the 1980s and early '90s, major music
labels held themselves up as free-speech champions as they fought
against pressure groups that were attacking specific songs. But
today, artists with explicit material are routinely asked to
re-sing lyrics, edit out particular words and even excise entire
songs from albums. And changes made to songs for radio play are
often far more extensive. By Neil Strauss.
</P>
