   &UR; BUSINESS &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LOOMING DISASTER FOR AMERICA'S MOBILE-PHONE INDUSTRY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOBILE-PHONE-THREAT-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ There are lots of reasons to question Deutsche
Telekom's $46.5-billion bid for VoiceStream, ranging from political
objections to its steep valuation of the American firm's customers.
But one of the most serious has hardly been mentioned. Deutsche
Telekom wants VoiceStream in part to win an America license for the
next generation of wireless services, known as 3G, which will carry
broadband data as well as voice. This is a looming disaster for
America's mobile-phone industry. The problem is that it has run out
of room to grow. &QL;
</P>
