Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   GAPOWER-SUIT _ Developing a follow on the Georgia Power lawsuit:
seeking an interview with Juanita Baranco, GaPower board member who
is heading the Diversity Council formed to respond to employee
allegations; also looking at a possible comparative analysis of the
Lockheed, Coke and GaPower lawsuits and, especially, the companies
reactions. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SCIENTIFIC-ATLANTA _ Scientific Atlanta is on a roll. The day
after reporting record 4th quarter earnings, it issued a prophecy
that it's first quarter would beat analysts' estimates by 13 cents
a share. Merrill Lynch upgraded its stock to a buy, and the shares
soared. ( Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FLIGHTSERV _Troubled flightserv.com announced a ``strategic
alliance'' with private investors who are bringing $2.5 million in
capital to the party. Checking what it means for the company's
struggling charter jet business. (thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ORKIN _ Internal memos written by Orkin Exterminating officials
acknowledge that company employees in several states, including
Georgia, falsified forms for reinspections of homes for termite
damage. The memos, obtained by the Journal-Constitution, say that
many customers ''are being charged for services not rendered.''
Orkin and its parent company, Atlanta-based Rollins Inc., are
targets of a Tampa lawsuit that alleges that Orkin workers
performed improper chemical treatments, skipped annual inspections,
forged customer names on inspection slips, and misrepresented
warranties, leading to widespread termite damage. Orkin faces a
similar lawsuit in Alabama that has reached class-action status.
The company denies the charges in each case. In addition, the
Florida attorney general's office is investigating Orkin's
advertising and warranty practices. Bob Buchner, a Florida
assistant attorney general, says five other states _ not Georgia _
are also investigating Orkin. (Miller, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
