A6412 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-WEB-RADIO30-COX     07-28 0428
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WEB-RADIO30-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Internet serves up truckloads of rude jawing, too
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 30.
 &HT;    By Russ DeVault
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Talk radio. It's not just for broadcast anymore. You can get it
on the Web, too.
</P>
<P>
   The hard-hitting, rude-boy antics of the Hot Talk radio format
are a big draw in other parts of the country. Though it hasn't made
it to the airwaves of Atlanta, you can get a taste on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   Hot Talk's most recognizable practitioner, Howard Stern, gets
the star treatment on the King of All Media site (www.koam.com).
It's not an official site, but a fan-produced tribute that's up to
date and informative. You can't actually hear Stern's show online
anywhere, but the site includes a hyperlinked list of radio
stations that carry it. There are audio files of clips from Stern's
show online, though, including a long list at Heynow's Web page
(www
</P>
<P>
   .angelfire.com/ny/heynow2). In Orlando, the popular WTKS-FM is
home to Hot Talk (www.wtks
</P>
<P>
   .com) and carries Stern's show.
</P>
<P>
   On the lighter side, eYada (eyada.com) dishes out entertainment
news and talk about movies, music and celebrity gossip. The site's
roster of hosts includes former Sex Pistol Johnny Rotten and the
New York Daily News husband-and-wife gossip team George Rush and
Joanna Molloy.
</P>
<P>
   Since this is the World Wide Web, you can even get talk radio in
a variety of tongues. Radio Romania International (www.rri.ro)
streams three channels of news, commentary and interviews in
Romanian. From Brazil, you can get news and sports in Portuguese
from Radio Gaucha (www.rdgaucha.com.br). The station's Web site
also has a list of several other Brazilian stations. For foreign
stations, one of the best online resources is Ituner
(www.ituner.com), with a clickable map that leads you to the
geographic location beneath your cursor.
</P>
<P>
   There's no need to go around the world for talk. You can get
local talk on your computer, too. Atlanta's own WSB (www
</P>
<P>
   .accessatlanta.com/partners
</P>
<P>
   /wsbradio) and The Zone/WQXI-AM 790 (www.790thezone.com), our
local sports-talk station, are both available on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   For a sampling of what's available in talk radio online,
BroadcastAmerica.com devotes a section to online radio chat that is
broken down by region and format (talk.broadcastamerica.com). You
can also get a list of talk stations and links at Real.com
(www.real.com).
</P>
<P>
   Russ DeVault writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
