<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-28 21:04 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6446 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v BC-BUDGET-SPI &LR;      07-28 0357
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, July 29, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Larry Johnson on the national-foreign desk at (206)
448-8035.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-CONVENTION (Washington) _ The Republican National
Convention, which begins Monday in Philadelphia, will be a big,
boisterous affair, expensive, tightly scripted, colorful and
occasionally dramatic. But is it important? Will it mean something
in the great democratic process? Or will it be a relic from another
era, an excuse for delegates to take a nice trip, to party and get
free political memorabilia?
</P>
<P>
   By Charles Pope. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BUCHANAN-PROFILE (Washington) _ Pat Buchanan is running hard for
president again, rebellious and incendiary as ever. But this time,
he's a rebel without a party _ the Republican Party.
</P>
<P>
   By Charles Pope. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   NADER-PROFILE (Undated) _ Ralph Nader has been mentioned as a
presidential candidate in each of the past four decades, but this
year, at the age of 66, he has finally taken to the campaign trail
in earnest. The consumer advocate and Green Party candidate is
campaigning against what he calls a ``government by global
corporations'' that has warped American democracy.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   POP-KDLANG (Undated) _ Singer-songwriter k.d. lang is enjoying
an invincible summer. ``Performing in the summertime is the very
best,'' lang says. ``There's lots of fresh air, you get to be
outside and you get rejuvenated by the sunshine.'' Summertime was
an appropriate time for lang to launch her latest tour. Her new
retro-pop album, ``Invincible Summer,'' was inspired by her move
several years ago to Southern California _ the land of endless
summers _ and several years of self-discovery.
</P>
<P>
   By Gene Stout. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ Seattle Mariners host Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Caple. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
</TEXT>
