<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GOP-CONVENTION-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; EDITORS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service is planning full coverage _
text, graphics and photos _ of the Republican National Convention
in Philadelphia from July 31 to Aug. 3.
</P>
<P>
   A biographical series on Gov. George W. Bush, written by New
York Times political writers, has been filed during the last two
months, and the stories are available for retransmission; the slugs
are: BUSH-BIO, BUSH-BIO-II, BUSH-BIO-III, BUSH-BIO-IV, BUSH-BIO-V,
BUSH-BIO-VI and BUSH-PARENTS; abridged versions and photos are
available. For repeats, call 212-556-1927.
</P>
<P>
   For the first two days of the convention, the Times editors plan
three to four pages of stories, which will then expand to five or
six daily pages. The News Service will list these stories on a
daily convention budget (BC-GOP-BUDGET-NYT), which will include all
Times stories and will also spotlight stories from Times partner
and regional newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   --Early coverage will include a profile of Laura Bush by Frank
Bruni, a reporter's notebook from the Bush campaign trail by Alison
Mitchell, and a poll/profile of the convention delegates by Adam
Nagourney.
</P>
<P>
   --Daily stories will include: a convention ledeall by Richard L.
Berke (GOP-RDP-NYT), a convention diary column by Matthew Purdy and
Alex Kuczynski (GOP-DAIRY-NYT), daily profiles on the speakers, a
television critic's notebook by Caryn James and editorial columns
from the Times writers on political developments and issues.
</P>
<P>
   --Plans for other stories include: analyses by R.W. Apple Jr.
(GOP-ASSESS-NYT), a story on the Republican platform by Robin
Toner, on Republicans in Congress by Adam Clymer, on the right wing
of the party by Robin Toner, on the Democratic ``truth squad'' by
Adam Nagourney and other color and voices features.
</P>
<P>
   --For Thursday: a Man in the News profile by Nicholas D. Kristof
and Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   --For Friday: a deconstruction of Bush's acceptance speech by
Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   All convention stories will be filed in the ``p'' category and
will carry a convention designation in the slug; e.g.,
BC-GOP-BUSH-NYT or BC-DEM-GORE-NYT. All stories are for use by New
York Times News Service clients. Look for updated and more detailed
advisories closer to the opening of the convention.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUESTIONS OR RERUNS: 888-346-9867 or 212-556-1927: &LR;
