<HEADLINE>
KANSAS CITY AREA GAS PRICES DOWN AGAIN THIS WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By GENE MEYER  
 c. 2000 Kansas City Star   KANSAS CITY, Mo _ Area gasoline prices
slipped another notch this week, to a metropolitan average of $1.39
a gallon for regular, AAA Automobile Club said in its latest Daily
Fuel Gauge report.
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Fuel Gauge estimate is taken from a daily sampling of prices
reported on charge card purchases. Auto club pollsters also conduct
a more formal survey each week by making firsthand price checks at
pumps.
</P>
<P>
   The latest change puts Kansas City area prices about midway
between the $1.63 prevailing a month ago at many pumps and the
$1.14 motorists paid this time last year.
</P>
<P>
   The chief reasons for the latest drop continue to be lower crude
oil and wholesale gasoline prices and another small increase in
fuel supplies, said Mike Right, AAA's chief spokesman in Missouri.
</P>
<P>
   Among other cities in the region that AAA checked, prices were
lowest in Wichita, Kan., at $1.33 a gallon compared with $1.70 a
month ago. Prices dropped the most in Topeka, Kan., to $1.38 a
gallon from $1.79 a month ago. St. Louis motorists are paying an
average of $1.40 a gallon, down 20 cents from a month ago, while
prices in Joplin, Mo., are down 22 cents to an average of $1.39.
( 30 )
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
